  <description>
  <![CDATA[
<p>PMD scans Java source code and looks for potential problems like:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Unused local variables</li>
  <li>Empty catch blocks</li>
  <li>Unnecessary object creation</li>
  <li>Empty 'if' statements</li>
  <li>Classes which could be Singletons</li>
  <li>Short/long variable and method names</li>
</ul>
<p>For example, here's the unused code that PMD found in the <a href="jdk14.HTML">JDK 1.4 source code</a>. Yikes!</p>
<p>You can get the current release, plugins for JEdit and JBuilder, and lots of other project information <a href="http://sf.net/projects/pmd/">here</a></p>
  ]]>
